The red, green, and brown, are too similar for the 8% of us with colorblindness to differentiate. Please change them to be more distinct. If you could tweak the css to something like the following we could actually see the state of the files without opening them.

#content-column span.frx-added, #navigation-tree .tree span.frx-added a {
    color: #14b93c;
}

#content-column span.frx-deleted, #navigation-tree .tree span.frx-deleted a {
    color: #d03417;
}

Thanks for your consideration.

